<LP>
   TORONTO -- Magna International Inc., an auto-parts
manufacturer, said it agreed to sell to a group of U.S.
institutional investors by way of private placement, $100
million of 10% convertible subordinated debentures due 2001.
   The debentures will be convertible into Class A
subordinate voting shares at $8.525 a share. The company
currently has about 26.5 million Class A shares outstanding.
The sale is expected to close next Tuesday.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Proceeds will be used to reduce debt.
</TEXT>
